HTML - Hyper text markup language

- To create a Web pages
- Not a programming language
- it is a markup language
- Every website can start with HTML

1. Heading - h - h1 to h6

2. Paragraph - p

3. hr

4. br

5. Text formatting - b or strong, u, mark, sup and sub.....

6. Anchor Tag - a

7. Image tag - img

8. list - order list and unorder list

9. tables - th, tr, td

10. forms
    input and Label

11. Media Elements
    audio and video

12. Sematic Tags - Header, footer, section, nav, and main

13. Division tag - div

CSS - Cascading Style Sheet

1. Type of CSS
   i - Inline
   ii - internal
   iii - Enternal
   Inline > Internal > External

2. CSS Syntax
   Selector{
   property:value;
   }

3. Types of Selectors
   i - Element selector - (h1), (h2), (p)
   ii - Class selector - (.) - Can use the same class name in multiple times, Number of times
   iii - id selector - (#) - Unique name only can apply the id, only one time
   iv - Universal selector - (\*) - Apply for the entire site
   v - group selector - Same class or id name and different types of tags can use the same style means we go with group selector

4. Colors and Background
   color: red;
   background-color: aqua;
   background-image: url(./Assets/Spider-man.webp);
   background-repeat: no-repeat;
   background-size: cover;
   background-position: center;

5. Text styling
   font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;
   font-size: 30px;
   text-align: center;
   text-transform: uppercase;
   text-decoration: underline;
   font-weight: bold;
   line-height: 1;
   letter-spacing: 1px;

6. Box Modeling
   Content
   padding
   border
   margin

7. Flex
8. Direction - Row, row-reverse, column, column-reverse
9. justify-content - (X) - Start, center, end, space-around, 3. space-between, space-evenly
10. align-items - (Y) - Start, center, end
11. Flex-wrap - nowrap, wrap, wrap-reverse
12. Align-content - (Y) (only flex wrap enable then only it will act) - Start, center, end, space-around, space-between, space-evenly
13. Flex (on items) - For grow the flex item
14. order - Change the visual order of the flex item
15. gap - to be assgin with values px,cm,m,%....

16. Position
17. Static (default)
18. Relative
19. Absolute
20. Fixed
21. Sticky

22. Grid
    2 - dimensional layout System

23. Transition and Animation
    1.Tranition - Whenever you can hover the effect will act
    transition-duration: 5s;
    transition-property: background-color;
    transition-timing-function: linear;
    transition-delay: 3s;

   transform- rotate, scale, translate
2.Animation - Just refresh the site it will happens
   animation-name: circle;
   animation-duration: 5s;
   animation-fill-mode: forwards; *
   animation-iteration-count: infinite;

   must - using @keyframes and give some limits like 50%, 100% or From and to...

24. Media Queries or Responsive design
  Mobile - 320px to 600px 
  tab    - 601px to 800px 
  lap/desktop - Above 801px  